cvs_key_vault_cmek_string.description: This output will present the CMEK string, which will be passed to the resources for either Platform and Self-Service Modules

cvs_key_vault_cmek_region.description: The region passed for the resource, to get the correct CMEK from the CVS Key Vault Projects

cvs_key_vault_dynamic_cmek.description: To use additional CVS Key Vault Project, other than the default ones (cvs-key-vault-prod & cvs-key-vault-nonprod). sql_database_deletion_policy.description: The deletion policy for the database

sql_database_id.description: Identifier for the resource with format projects/{{project}}/instances/{{instance}}/databases/{{name}}

sql_database_name.description: The name of the database in the Cloud SQL instance

sql_database_self_link.description: The URI of the created resource

sql_database_charset.description: The charset value. See MySQL's Supported Character Sets and Collations and Postgres' Character Set Support for more details and supported values. Postgres databases only support a value of UTF8 at creation time

sql_database_collation.description: The collation value. See MySQL's Supported Character Sets and Collations and Postgres' Collation Support for more details and supported values. Postgres databases only support a value of en_US.UTF8 at creation time

sql_database_deletion_policy.description: The deletion policy for the database. Setting ABANDON allows the resource to be abandoned rather than deleted. This is useful for Postgres, where databases cannot be deleted from the API if there are users other than cloudsqlsuperuser with access. Possible values are: 'ABANDON', 'DELETE'. Defaults to 'DELETE'

sql_database_instance.description: The name of the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID

sql_database_name.description: The name of the database in the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID or instance name

sql_database_project.description: The ID of the project in which the resource belongs

sql_database_instance_connection_name.description: The connection name of the instance to be used in connection strings

sql_database_instance_database_version.description: Supported values include: MYSQL_5_6, MYSQL_5_7, MYSQL_8_0, POSTGRES_9_6,POSTGRES_10, POSTGRES_11, POSTGRES_12, POSTGRES_13, POSTGRES_14, POSTGRES_15, SQLSERVER_2017_STANDARD, SQLSERVER_2019_STANDARD, SQLSERVER_2022_STANDARD

sql_database_instance_deletion_protectio.description: Whether or not to allow Terraform to destroy the instance. Unless this field is set to false in Terraform state, a terraform destroy or terraform apply command that deletes the instance will fail. Defaults to true

sql_database_instance_encryption_key_nam.description: The full path to the encryption key used for the CMEK disk encryption

sql_database_instance_instance_type.description: The type of the instance. The supported values are SQL_INSTANCE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED, CLOUD_SQL_INSTANCE, ON_PREMISES_INSTANCE and READ_REPLICA_INSTANCE

sql_database_instance_private_ip_address.description: The first private (PRIVATE) IPv4 address assigned

sql_database_instance_self_link.description: The URI of the created resource

sql_database_instance_service_account_em.description: The service agent email address assigned to the instance, which is created by Google and is not passable as a variable

sql_database_instance_setttings_edition.description: Supported values include: MYSQL_5_6, MYSQL_5_7, MYSQL_8_0, POSTGRES_9_6,POSTGRES_10, POSTGRES_11, POSTGRES_12, POSTGRES_13, POSTGRES_14, POSTGRES_15, SQLSERVER_2017_STANDARD, SQLSERVER_2019_STANDARD, SQLSERVER_2022_STANDARD

sql_database_instance_dynamic_database_f.description: Flags that users can pass dynamically, but still pass teh security required flags

sql_database_instance_encryption_key_nam.description: The full path to the encryption key used for the CMEK disk encryption. Setting up disk encryption currently requires manual steps outside of Terraform. The provided key must be in the same region as the SQL instance

sql_database_instance_project.description: The ID of the project in which the resource belongs

sql_database_instance_region.description: The region the instance will sit in

sql_database_instance_settings_availabil.description: The availability type of the Cloud SQL instance, high availability (REGIONAL) or single zone (ZONAL).' For all instances, ensure that settings.backup_configuration.enabled is set to true. For MySQL instances, ensure that settings.backup_configuration.binary_log_enabled is set to true. For Postgres and SQL Server instances, ensure that settings.backup_configuration.point_in_time_recovery_enabled is set to true. Defaults to ZONAL

sql_database_instance_settings_backup_co.description: Depending on the value of retention_unit, this is used to determine if a backup needs to be deleted. If retention_unit is 'COUNT', we will retain this many backups
The unit that 'retained_backups' represents. Defaults to COUNT
True if backup configuration is enabled
The region where the backup will be stored
HH:MM format time indicating when backup configuration starts
The number of days of transaction logs we retain for point in time restore, from 1-7

sql_database_instance_settings_deletion_.description: Enables deletion protection of an instance at the GCP level

sql_database_instance_settings_disk_auto.description: Enables auto-resizing of the storage size. Defaults to true
The maximum size to which storage capacity can be automatically increased. The default value is 0, which specifies that there is no limit

sql_database_instance_settings_disk_size.description: The size of data disk, in GB. Size of a running instance cannot be reduced but can be increased. The minimum value is 10GB

sql_database_instance_settings_disk_type.description: The type of data disk: PD_SSD or PD_HDD. Defaults to PD_SSD

sql_database_instance_settings_ip_config.description: Name = A name for this whitelist entry, Value = A CIDR notation IPv4 or IPv6 address that is allowed to access this instance. Must be set even if other two attributes are not for the whitelist to become active. Format {key = value}

The VPC network from which the Cloud SQL instance is accessible for private IP. For example, projects/myProject/global/networks/default. Specifying a network enables private IP. At least ipv4_enabled must be enabled or a private_network must be configured. This setting can be updated, but it cannot be removed after it is set

sql_database_instance_settings_maintenan.description: Day of week (1-7), starting on Monday
Hour of day (0-23), ignored if day not set

sql_database_instance_settings_pricing_p.description: Pricing plan for this instance, can only be PER_USER

sql_database_instance_settings_user_labe.description: A set of key/value user label pairs to assign to the instance

sql_database_instance_trusted_client_cer.description: Whether or not the user is bring a Trusted Client Certificate, which will determine the ssl configuration. True means SQL Instance will use a Trusted Client Certificate. False means the SQL Instance will only use SSL and not verify a certificate. True or False, SSL is enabled

sql_user_host.description: The host the user can connect from. This is only supported for BUILT_IN users in MySQL instances. Don't set this field for PostgreSQL and SQL Server instances. Can be an IP address. Changing this forces a new resource to be created

sql_user_name.description: The name of the user. Changing this forces a new resource to be created

sql_user_password.description: The password for the user. Can be updated. For Postgres instances this is a Required field, unless type is set to either CLOUD_IAM_USER or CLOUD_IAM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT. sql_user_password_policy_enable_password.description: If true, the user must specify the current password before changing the password. This flag is supported only for MySQL

sql_user_password_policy_password_expira.description: Password expiration duration with one week grace period
